The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Ivanov, Poll dropped

Berlin: English referee Graham Poll and Russias Valentin Ivanov paid the price for their performances during the first round of the World Cup by being dropped from the remainder of the competition on Thursday. 

Fifas Referees Committee announced in Frankfurt the names of 12 teams of referees and their linesmen in contention to take charge of the remaining eight matches of the competition. 

The list includes Germanys Markus Merk, who was involved in a public spat with Australias Harry Kewell after their first round match against Brazil finished in a 2-0 win to the world champions. 

 (AGENCIES) 




